        <div xml:id="textSource">
            <head>Poem: </head>
            <p><author>Charles-Hubert Millevoye</author> (<date>1782–1816</date>), <title
                    xml:lang="fr">La Fauvette</title> in <title xml:lang="fr">Poésies
                Légères</title>. <biblStruct><title rend="italics" xml:lang="fr">Œuvres complètes,
                        3e éd., </title><date>1827</date>, <biblScope type="tome">tome <num
                            value="1">I</num></biblScope>, <biblScope type="pp">p.
                    282–23</biblScope>.</biblStruct> The poem is not called <title>Vieille
                Chanson</title>.</p>
        </div>

        <div xml:id="history">
            <head>Composition: </head>
            <p>by <date type="composition">1865</date>, when it was published. The autographs
                suggest it was originally presented as the work of another. Gaston de Betzi was
                Bizet’s occasional pseudonym (see <title>Hymne à la paix</title>).</p>
        </div>

